name: Fifth Gear
overview: Getting viewers up to speed on all the latest automotive information, with new car reviews, second hand bargains and industry tidbits being the focus of this magazine show.

seasons.name: Season 25
seasons.overview: A motor magazine with the recent driving news, expert opinions, and practical & reliable advices. The hosts have motorsport backgrounds and take you under the hoods of the latest speedsters and conduct tests and stunts to see what different cars are capable of [+]more

seasons.name: Season 28
seasons.overview: Series 28 sees regulars Jason Plato, Vicki Butler-Henderson, Jonny Smith and Jimmy De Ville as they test, review and compare a huge range of cars, from hot hatchbacks to versatile 4x4s and more.  Also new to the team, ex-F1 driver Karun Chandhok will add his talent and experience to put a host of cars through their paces.

seasons.name: Season 29
seasons.overview: In the new series, team is behind the wheel of the latest EVs and ICE cars in Fifth Gear favourite features like team tests and shootouts. Hosts Jason Plato and Vicki Butler-Henderson will be joined by Rory Reid, ex-Top Gear presenter Grace Webb, and engineering ace Jimmy de Ville.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Adrian Simpson test drives Hyundai Coupe (Tiburon in the US). Vicki Butler-Henderson Test Drives BMW F650 Motorcycle while learning to go off-road. Tiff Needell test drives Subaru Impreza STI and Mitsubishi Lancer Evo 7. Tom Ford Talks about classic Hot Rods at the Spring nationals. Tiff Needell test drives the VW Phaeton.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Vicki Butler-Henderson Test Drives the Ford Focus ST. Quentin Wilson Test the effects of marijuana while driving. Tiff Needell Drives Tiger Z-100 to braek the 0-60mph time from 3.0 seconds with 2.97 seconds. Adrian Simpson drives the Ford Model T Video of a modified Ford F350 SUV called the "Smart Truck" used for protecting dignitaries from terrorist.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Tiff Needell test drives a Pagani Zhonda. Quentin Wilson test drives a cheap used 1992 BMW 318i. Adrian Simpson Talks about large American SUVs and Trucks. Guest Star: Tim Westwood. skooda guy talks about his cars. Adrian Simpson test drives the Mercedes-Benz E-Class.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Tiff Needell test drives a MG-FT. Quentin Wilson Talks about how different people try to get away from speeding tickets caught by speed cameras. Adrian Simpson test drives a modern remake of Triumph TR5. Vicki Butler-Henderson races around in the "Lo Cost" racing series, Finished 14th. Tom Ford test drives VW Polo, Seat Ibiza, and the Ford Fiesta.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Arian Simpson test drives Vauxhall Vectra. Tiff Needell helps Liz a new mini owner how to race a mini in the "John Copper" Racing Series finished 14th. Quentin Wilson test drives a Mercedes-Benz 500SL and a Jaguar XK8. Tiff Needell Talks to Tom Chilton about being the youngest person to win the British Touring Car Championship.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Arian Simpson test drives Renault Vel Satis. Quentin Wilson test drives a Liquid Petroleum Gas (LPG) powered car. Vicki Butler-Henderson test drives an Audi A4. Quentin Wilson test drives a Ford KA. Tiff Needell and Vicki Butler-Henderson race i a radical racing series, Finish 9th.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: Tiff Needell and Vicki Butler-Henderson show how men and women differ while driving and parking.

episodes.name: Series 2, Episode 1
episodes.overview: Vicki Butler-Henderson, Adrian Simpson, and Tom Ford visit the Paris motor show. They look at many of the new models revealed, including the Porsche Cayenne and Bentley Continental GT.

episodes.name: Series 2, Episode 2
episodes.overview: Tiff Needell travels to California to test Nissan's new 350Z sports car. Is it a worthy successor to the company's 1970s 240Z? And is it as good to drive as it looks? Tiff thinks so.

episodes.name: Series 2, Episode 3
episodes.overview: Adrian Simpson test drives Volvo's new off-roader. He concludes because of their attention to safety, the environment, and the family-size accommodation, Volvo has created a different kind of 4x4.

episodes.name: Series 2, Episode 4
episodes.overview: Quentin Willson, Tiff Needell, Vicki Butler-Henderson, and Adrian Simpson visit the British International Motorshow. They look at some of the cars they didn't see at the recent Paris show.

episodes.name: Series 2, Episode 5
episodes.overview: Tiff Needell tests a comprehensive selection of the latest hot hatches including the new and long-awaited Ford Focus RS. He rules out the MGZR, the Mini Cooper S, and the Renault Clio Cup.

episodes.name: Series 2, Episode 6
episodes.overview: Tiff Needell poses the question, "What's the best GT car you can buy for £90,000?" He tests the top contenders which both come from Stuttgart - the Mercedes SL55 AMG and the Porsche 911 Turbo.

episodes.name: Series 2, Episode 7
episodes.overview: Multi-millionaire John Caudwell, the boss of a mobile phone company, has a budget of £500,000 to spend on new cars and he's come to Fifth Gear for some advice on what motors to choose.

episodes.name: Series 2, Episode 8
episodes.overview: Tom Ford tests Nissan's new Micra. He finds it well-made and easy to drive. Adrian Simpson goes in search of haunted cars. He starts by being very skeptical that haunted cars can exist at all.

episodes.name: Ultimate Crash Test
episodes.overview: Tiff and Quentin recreate crash tests you don't typically see, using remote control cars at almost 120mph. Quentin also tests out the Rolls-Royce and Vicki tests out the Ford StreetKA.

episodes.name: Exploding Cars
episodes.overview: Using members of the public and our presenters, we test whether it’s worse to drive drunk or drive tired. Also the highlights from the Geneva Show (Back in 2003) featuring Aston Martin, Lamborghini, the Porsche Carrera GT,the 5-series and X3 BMWs.

episodes.name: Roll-Over
episodes.overview: We demonstrate how cars explode in the films, we show how they can catch fire then we re-create our own stunt. Tiff road tests the Jaguar XJ and then visit Aston Martin’s Works service Department.

episodes.name: Series 3, Episode 4
episodes.overview: In this episode of Fifth Gear, we answer the question of who is a better driver – men or women – each going through different tests of parking, manoeuvring and travelling to see which gender is best.

episodes.name: Bullet Proof Cars
episodes.overview: Tiff looks into how cars are made bullet-proof and how to drive out of a sticky situation. Also road testing the VW Touareg, one of the world's most powerful 4x4's.

episodes.name: Road Rage
episodes.overview: We frighten the living daylights out of Adrian on this 200mph go kart with a rocket afterburner, and Tiff tests the Zonda Cabrio, Evo 8/ Impreza, Clio V6 all driven on some of the planet’s best roads.

episodes.name: World's Greatest Sports Cars
episodes.overview: The team showcase the world greatest sports cars, how to drive them professionally and which sports car is the best!

episodes.name: Series 3, Episode 8
episodes.overview: Are 4x4's as safe as you think? We put that to the test with a high speed crash test. Adrian is in a £250k limo and Tom tests out the BMW 5 Series.

episodes.name: Series 3, Episode 9
episodes.overview: We see the worst of road rage, test out the BMW 5-Series and Peugeot 206 Gti 180.

episodes.name: Series 3, Episode 10
episodes.overview: We look into the world of car chases in film! Featuring The Matrix, the BMW series "The Hire" and the ultimate British TV classic The Sweeney!

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview:
Vicky and Tiff find out what happens when you crash an old model of a car into a new model of a car and which fairs better.

Guest presenter Jason Plato (a British touring car champion) drives the new Ferrari 612 Scaglietti.

Tiff finds out which is fastest, the Citroën C2 GT or the Ford Sport Ka.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview:
Adrian reviews the new Audi A6 in Italy.

A lookback at past car versus plane races - includes the race of Michael Schumacher in his Ferrari F1 race car versus a Euro Fighter.

Vicki goes to the Geneva Auto Show and checks out some cool cars - BMW Concept M5, Honda Sports Concept (new NSX?), Rolls-Royce 100EX, Land Rover concept Range Stormer; Fiat concept Trepiuno and Maserati MC12.

Tiff races a Gazelle helicopter around a track in a Porsche GT3.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview:
Tiff talks about some people’s fear of driving and with some help from a car psychologist, helps cure a woman of her fears.

Tom reviews the awesome Aston Martin DB9, the best Aston Martin yet.

Vicki gets some NOS and makes a diesel Golf compete with a Honda NSX driven by Tiff.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview:
Tiff and Vicki show what happens when tires blow, whether run flats are really any good and whether you can race on run flats.

Tom reviews the new Mercedes-Benz SLK.

Tiff sees which is faster around a track - a Mini Cooper or a diesel Skoda Fabia.

Vicki drives that British amphibious vehicle, the Gibbs Aquada.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview:
Vicki, Adrian and Tom go out and look for the ultimate Mini and come across some very cool mini’s.

Tiff goes to Malaga in the south of Spain to drive Klaas Zwart’s supercar, the Ascari KZ1 at his supercar track resort.

Tom talks about the new Land Rover Discovery.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview:
Tom goes to Maranello, Italy to see Frank Mountain buy and drive Michael Schumacher’s 2001 F1 car.

Tiff drives the new version of the Noble M12 GTO, the 3R.

Adrian visits one of Britain’s most secure car parks, the Bold Lane and shows how it works.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview:
Tiff and Vicki find the best 4×4 available in Britain for under £20,000.

Returning guest presenter Jason Plato (a British touring car champion) drives the Chrysler 300C which has a Hemi!

Adrian goes and meets Richard Hopkins, one of the top players in “World Rally Champonship 3″ for the Playstation 2 who is now trying out real rally racing.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview:
Vicki and Tom head to Italy to test the new Maserati Quattroporte.

Tiff talks about car jumps and the science of it followed by a stunt driver trying to break the world record for the farthest distance jumped by a car towing a caravan.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview:
Tiff and Vicki go and visit Jay Kay from Jamiroquai (some British band I think) to view his car collection and race around in some buggies.

Tom reviews the new Peugeot 407.

Fifth Gear Shootout: Tiff races two vans against each other - a Ford Transit T280 and a Mercedes-Benz Sprinter 213 CD1.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview:
Fifth Gear checks out the British auto show - the Motor Show at Birmingham NEC.

Tom drives the new Volkswagen Beetle convertable.

Fifth Gear Shootout: Tiff races the Lotus Elise 111R against the Lotus built Vauxhall VX220 Turbo.

Adrian trys out Internet auto auctions.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview:
Tiff finds out which is fastest - a car, a motorcycle, or a boat.

Jason Plato reviews the new BMW 1 Series.

Vicki talks about why she loves the Ford Capri and why it’s such a good car.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview:
Tiff reviews the Mercedes-Benz SLR McLaren and drives it on the test track.

Jason Plato drives the new Ford Focus.

Vicki examines how private enforcement companies are issuing parking tickets in Britain.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview:
Vicki, Tiff and Jason find which economical - a diesel, a gasoline, or a hybrid powered car.

Tiff drives the new Porsche 911 Carrera S.

Fifth Gear Shootout: Tiff in a Lamborghini Gallardo vs. Kevin Smith on a Ducati 999 motorcycle.

ATV vs. car crash footage.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview:
Tiff and Vicki talk about the Smart car and how it does in crashes.

Vicki drives the Vauxhall Tigra, a hard top convertible.

Jason goes to Modena to pick up a Ferrari 575 Handling GTC and then drives it to the Nüburgring for some hot laps.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Tiff and Vicki find the best cars built in Britain featuring the new Mini, TVR T350, Noble M12, Bentley Continental GT, Aston Martin DB9, Vauxhall VX220 Turbo, Lotus Elise, Range Rover, Land Rover Defender, Rolls Royce Phantom, and others.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview:
Tiff teaches Chris Ryan, former SAS commando, how to drive quickly around a track and to powerslide.

Vicki tries to hit 200 MPH in the new Aston Martin Vanquish S.

Adrian drives the new Seat Toledo.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview:
Jason drives the new Volkswagen Golf GTI 

Vicki and Tom make their pick for the best MPV aka minivan.

Tiff sits down and talks with Jackie Stewart, a triple World Champion with 27 Grand Prix victories.

Fifth Gear Shootout: MG ZT vs. Vauxhall Monaro.

Vicki narrates a motorcycle vs. car crash test.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview:
Tom does a great review of the new Land Rover Discovery.

Fifth Gear Shootout: Smart Brabus Roadster Coupe vs. Mini Cooper S Convertable.

Vicki examines a classic Porsche 911 Carrera 3.2 .

Tiff, Vicki and Jason start working on their project to make a non-supercar reach 200 MPH.

Fifth Gear’s new sport - Caravan Rallycross.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview:
Jason does the very first TV review in the world of the Ferrari F430.

Fifth Gear Shootout: Not wanting to let a motorcycle be the fastest around the track, Tiff takes a Mosler MT900S around the track.

Tom drives the European version of the Nissan Murano.

Tiff and Vicki examine what happens when a car his a pedestrian.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview:
Best small car.

Best family car.

Best fast car.

An overall Fifth Gear car of the year is chosen.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview:
Tiff drives the new Porsche Boxster and goes against Jason driving his BMW Z4 to compare the two.

New presenter, Jon Bentley, looks into GPS based speed camera detectors.

Vicki learns how to be a stuntman from a professional.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview:
Jason drives the new BMW 3 series on a 1000 mile, 48 hour road trip through Spain and France.

Fifth Gear Shootout: Vicki compares the Mercedes-Benz SLK 55 AMG to the Mercedes-Benz SL55.

Tiff flys to Northern Sweden to try out some winter driving in a Jaguar and shows how well ABS, traction control, and the electronic stability program (ESP) work.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview:
Vicki drives the new Mercedes-Benz A 200, compares it’s quality to the Mercedes-Benz SL 500, and compares it to the BMW 1 Series.

Tiff attends the launch party for Gran Turismo 4, drives the Toyota Supra race car from the game a little, checks out how realistic the game is, and then races head to head with the game’s designer.

Jason goes to Dubai to check out A1 Grand Prix and to race one of the cars around the new race track there.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview:
Jason checks out the new TVR Sargaris and TVR Tuscan 2 and races them with Vicki.

Tom drives the new Fiat Panda 4×4 and races it against a Range Rover.

The Fifth Gear crew return to their 200 MPH car project and continue work on their 1999 Lotus Esprit V8 GT.

Tiff meets up with the VMax car club and rides with 19 year-old Adam in his dad’s RUF Porsche 911 to try to hit 200 MPH.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview:
Tiff examines the new Range Rover Sport and races it a horse.

Vicki sees if her mom can get around the Anglesey race circuit in under 1 minute 30 seconds in the new automatic Lamborghini Murcielago.

Tom takes a ride in Frank Mountain’s new £500,000 Maserati MC12 on a snow-bound circuit and witnesses Frank hit a wall.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview:
Tiff and Jason compare the Dodge Viper SRT-10 and the Corvette C6.

Vicki drives the new contest car, a classic 1964 Volkswagen Beetle 1300.

Tom tests an Ariel Atom 2 that has 300 horsepower thanks to a supercharger and then takes it through a car wash.

Jon Bentley examines a new, safer type of lamp post and what happens when you crash into a regular style pole vs. the new style.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview:
Tom examines the new Peugeot 1007 which has sliding doors.

Fifth Gear Shootout: Vicki races the Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution MR FQ 400 with its sophisticated electronics against the Noble M400.

 

Jon compares diesel powered cars to those powered by gasoline and explains what the advantages of each are.

Tiff teams up with British supermodel Jodie Kidd to go racing in the Maserati Trofeo series.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview:
Jason drives the new Jeep Grand Cherokee 

Vicki drives the £85,000, 207 MPH Superformance Le Mans Coupe, a replica of the Shelby Daytona Coupe.

Fifth Gear Shootout: Tiff races two hot hatches, the Honda Civic Type-R versus the Renault Clio 182.

Jon Bentley examines what happens in crash compatibility problems - where cars with different bumper heights and strengths collide like with a SUV and a small car.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview:
Fifth Gear Shootout: Tiff finds out which is quickest, the Porsche Cayenne or the BMW X5.

Jon finds out what Britains think the most prestigious car in Britain is.

Vicki drives the new Citroen C4 VTS.

Tiff follows a competition where the Renault Formula 1 team will choose one young person to become a new engineer on their team.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview:
Tiff drives the incredible new BMW M5 to the famous Pau circuit in the South of France.

With MG Rover having gone out of business recently, Vicki examines which models are good deals with the serious dealer discounts.

Jason goes to Monaco to check out the Top Marques Monaco Motorshow, a motorshow for high rollers featuring tons of really expensive cars including the Pagani Zonda F, Bugatti Veyron, and others as well as a £20 million yacht.

While in Monaco, gets an exclusive look at the £300,000 Venturi Fetish, a radical new sportscar, and then bumps into former James Bond and Monaco resident Roger Moore who is interested in buying one.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview:
A preview of things to come this season on Fifth Gear.

Tiff drives the new Aston Martin V8 Vantage and tests it out on a race track, sideways as usual.

Tom goes to an exclusive auction held by Ferrari where tons of rare and expensive Ferrari related items were sold off.

Tiff examines the Mazda SASSOU concept car.

Fifth Gear Shootout: Vicki races the Porsche 911 Carrera S against the Lotus Exige 240R.

Jason finds out if fighter pilots make good drivers and if drivers make good fighter pilots by going flying in a Harrier and by taking a pilot around the track in a Ford GT.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview:
Tiff driving a Williams FW26 Formula 1 Grand Prix car races Vicki in a BMW M5, Jason tests the Pagani Zonda F and Jon Bentley discovers what it's like to hit a newly designed safe sign post.

This episode's shootout is between the Mitsubishi Evo IX and the older Mitsubishi Evo VI.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview:
Tom tests the Bentley Flying Spur, Tiff drives the 806bhp Koenigsegg CCR and competes with Vicki in the first 24 hour race at Silverstone.

This episode's shootout is between the Westfield XTR4 and the Suzuki GXR1000.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview:
Tom attends the Goodwood Festival of Speed where he drives the Maserati Birdcage concept car and Ferrari 575 Superamerica, Vicki challenges Michael Schumacher to an fuel economy race and Jason tests the new Mercedes S Class.

This episode's shootout is between the Ford Fiesta ST 150 and the Mitsubishi Colt CZT.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview:
Vicki says goodbye to the Honda NSX, Jason reviews the Aston Martin DB9 Volante and the latest report on Fifth Gear's project to build a 200mph car.

This episode's shootout is between the Mazda RX-8 and the Alfa GT V6.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview:
Tiff tests the Ferrari F430 Spider, guest host Charley Boorman attends the 2005 Motorcycle and Scooter Show and Vicki drives a BMW M5 with her eyes closed.

This episode's shootout is between the Nissan 350Z and the Audi TT.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview:
Tom reviews the Mercedes R Class SUV, Tiff drives the BMW M6, Vicki tests the new Mazda MX-5 and Jason tries his hand as a trader.

This episode's shootout is between the Suzuki Swift and the Peugeot Jetforce 125 scooter.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview:
Jason tests the Ford Focus ST, Tiff tackles a would be London Grand Prix circuit in a Studio G 350, Tom reviews the Lexus IS220d and Vicki driving a Dodge RAM SRT-10 races Chris Vermeulen in a 1933 Ford Coupe.

This episode's shootout is between the Mercedes CLS 55 AMG and the Jaguar XJR.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview:
Tiff tests the Porsche Cayman S on Britain's most dangerous road, Tom reviews the new Honda Civic and Jason attempts to sell his car for a profit.

This episode's shootout is between the Volvo V50 T5 and the Legacy 3.0R Spec B Sports Tourer.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview:
Jason drives the Lamborghini Gallardo SE 

Tiff speed tests 3 cars: the Nissan Micra C+C, the Seat Leon, and the Mercedes-Benz ML.

The Fifth Gear crew tells who’s won the content cars so far this season.

Jon Bentley reviews some portable satellite navigation systems.

Fifth Gear Shootout: Tiff races two classic 80’s cars, the BMW E30 M3 and the Lancia Delta Integrale.

And finally, the annual Fifth Gear Awards where Fifth Gear announces their "Car of the Year".

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview:
Jason helps a lottery winner choose his dream car, Tiff tests the Jaguar XK and Tom reports from the Geneva Motor Show.

This episode's shootout is between the first and latest generation of the Mazda MX-5.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview:
Tiff and Jason compete against each other in 50's style Le Mans racers, Tom tests the Audi Q7 and Paul Dalton shows the clinical precision with which he cleans and polishes a car.

This episode's shootout is between the Subaru Impreza STi and the Subaru Forrester STi.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview:
Vicki drives the Ferrari F430 Challenge, Jason drives the BMW Z4M Roadster, Tom experiences what it's like to buy a Maybach and Tiff takes part in the G4 Challenge.

This episode's shootout is between the Ford Focus ST and the Vauxhall Astra VXR.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview:
Tom visits America's most exclusive supercar club, Tiff and Jason test the Audi RS4 and BMW M3 CS on the track and Vicki drives the Alfa Romeo Brera.

This episode's shootout is between the Mercedes A200T and the Toyota Verso T180.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Tiff tests a Ford GT40 replica, Jason drives the Audi S6 on the German Autobahns, Tiff and Vicki attempts to find Britain's best small car and Peter Saywell reveals his supercar collection.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview:
Tiff heads to Italy to drive the latest version of the Maserati Quattroporte, the Sport GT which features a much better gearbox.

Jason gives the girls of the pop group Girls Aloud a lesson in driving supercars on a racing circuit which ends in a crash (who woulda guessed?).

Jon Bentley investigates how young drivers can get cheaper insurance rates.

Fifth Gear Shootout: Vicki races the BMW M5 against the BMW M6.

Tom participates in a world record attempt for the most number of cars doing donuts simultaneously.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview:
Fifth Gear follows around Britain’s leading automotive spy photographer for a day to see what his life is like.

Jason drives the new Volkswagen Eos, a hard top convertible, in Athens.

Guest presenter Holly Samos reports from the start line of the Gumball 3000.

Fifth Gear Reverse Gear Shootout: Tiff races a Volkswagen Golf GTi against a Skoda Octavia vRS, all in reverse gear!

Tom drives the fuel cell powered Honda FCX 

Tiff learns that not all American cars are crap thanks to the Chevrolet Corvette Z06.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview:
Vicki tests out how reliable a 16 year-old Mercedes E Class estate (station wagon) by giving it some very serious punishment.

Tom visits a service station in Tokyo where at night, some crazy cars show up for a car party 

Behind the scenes of the car stunts in M:I:III (Mission Impossible: III).

A look at the day in the life of Nick Freeman, a hugely successful defense lawyer who’s been dubbed “Mr. Loophole” because of his ability find holes in the law.

Tiff gives the brand new 620 horsepower Ferrari 599 GTB Fiorano a thrashing about in Italy.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview:
Jason drives the Lexus GS450h, the first high performance hybrid.

Tom sees if 22 people can cram into the new Fiat Grande Punto, a small city car.

An update on the winners of all of the cars given away this season by Fifth Gear.

A small teaser trailer of a segment that will shown later in the year of behind the scenes of the new James Bond film, Casino Royale, and the new James Bond car, the Aston Martin DBS.

Tiff races an Aston Martin DBR9 at Silverstone in the brand new GT3 Championship, against rivals driving Ferraris, Porsches, Lamborghinis, Corvettes, Maseratis, and Ascaris.

Jon Bentley looks into what happens if you put the wrong fuel type into your car.

Vicki races a gas (petrol) powered Vauxhall Astra VXR against a tuned diesel powered one driven by Paul O’Neill, an aspiring racing driver and brother of former Spice Girl, Melanie Chisholm (Sporty Spice).

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview:
Fifth Gear Shootout: Tiff races a BMW 130i M Sport against a Volkswagen Golf R32.

Tom examines the new Citroen C6 and gets driven around by Tiff while having a flat tire.

Vicki does some budget racing in Rallycross 

Jason drives the latest generation of the Honda Legend and pits it against it’s rivals, the Audi A6 and a BMW 530i.

Guest presenter Tim Lovejoy asks Carl and Didz from the rock band Dirty Pretty Things to pass judgement on the new Radford Mini.

Tom’s final report from Japan where this time he visits the world’s largest car dealership which is actually more like a theme park than an actual car dealership.

Vicki finishes off the Mercedes E Class from a previous episode.

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview:
Vicki attempts to set a new world record for the most distance traveled in one hour by seven people in a mini-MPV (minivan).

Tiff races a Dakar rally BMW motorcycle with it’s BMW X5 support vehicle to see which would win on a known offroad course, the 4×4 or the motorcycle.

Jon Bentley gives a 60 second driving review of the Volkswagen EcoRacer.

Tom flies to Austria in Alan Sugar’s private jet to test drive the new Audi TT on the road up Austria’s highest mountain, Großglockner.

Conclusion of the Fifth Gear concept car competition where the winner is announced.

Tiff learns to drift and enters the UK’s inaugural Drifting competition, the D1GP, in a 590 BHP 1991 Toyota Soarer which is fitted with a turbo from a truck.

Jason drives the very quick Brook Double R, a brand new British sportscar which is styled like a 60’s grand prix racer, on Britain’s bendiest road.

episodes.name: Episode 12
episodes.overview:
Vicki examines all things braking including the differences between different people when it comes to braking and how much worn tires affect your braking in the wet.

Jason drives the awesome new Porsche 911 Turbo.

Behind the scenes of The Fast and the Furious: Tokyo Drift.

Tiff teaches Tom to drive a Lamborghini Gallardo really fast around a track in order to bring his skills up to the Fifth Gear standards.

Jon Bentley checks out the top three ultimate car sound systems and evaluates each.

Vicki races two small pickup trucks, the Mitsubishi L200 and the Nissan Navara (aka the Nissan Frontier), against each other offroad.

episodes.name: Episode 13
episodes.overview:
Vicki tests the limited edition BMW 320Si which was made to celebrate BMW’s success in the World Touring Car Championships.

Jason finds out if the skills of a racing driver will transfer to the cockpit of a aerobatic stunt plane.

Tiff drives a race-spec McLaren F1 and a Ferrari Enzo on public roads.

Behind the scenes of the Pixar film Cars.

Jon Bentley examines a new safety device for motorcyclists, an airbag jacket.

Tom drives the new Ferrari 599 1200 miles from Belgium back home to the Ferrari factory in Italy.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Fifth Gear Jason Plato drives the awesome 500bhp Ford Shelby GT500; Vicki Butler-Henderson races the ultra-exclusive MINI GP against a 90mph radio-controlled car; Tom Ford tests the Skoda Roomster.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Fifth Gear Tom Ford is testing the opulent £225,000 Bentley Azure with some help from film director Michael Winner; Jonny Smith tries to drive coast to coast using chip fat as fuel.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview:
Guy Smith, a Le Mans winner, races in a Volkswagen Transporter Sportline against Tiff in an A-Team GMC van replica (I assume / hope it’s a replica).

Superbike racer Shakey Byrne goes to Italy to drive the new Lamborghini Murcielago LP640.

Vicki teaches her older sister how to race a Lotus Elise S around a circuit.

Tim Lovejoy takes to the streets of London in an electric car called the G Wiz in an effort to find out if it’s practical or not.

Tom Ford drives the very odd looking Skoda Roomster.

Jon Bentley investigates how safe the ramped ends of motorway crash barriers are by driving a car into one.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview:
Jason Plato is back and he’s teaching England cricketer Kevin Pietersen how to race in a Lamborghini Gallardo Spyder.

Tim Lovejoy hangs out with GQ magazine editor and style guru Dylan Jones to find out what cars are considered cool for the modern man.

Tom Ford heads to Barcelona to drive the all-new version of the new Mini.

Another installment of “Wreck My Ride”, this time with a 1993 Fiat Cinquecento.

Jonny Smith checks out the world’s fastest street legal car — a highly modified Vauxhall Victor.

Vicki drives the Nissan Murano Grand Tourer Concept, a super sporty SUV that supposedly drives like a sports car.

The master Tiff works his magic on the Lamborghini Gallardo Spyder.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview:
Jason powerslides an imported Ford Shelby Mustang GT500 around a track.

Vicki races a 1050 HP racing semi-truck 

Tiff tries out the new Suzuki Swift Sport.

Now that Quad bikes are road legal in the UK, Tom tries one out on the road.

Tim rides along with some traffic police.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview:
Jason drives the brand new Lotus Europa S.

Fifth Gear pick their top 5 favorite Bond car chases with some commentary from Sir Roger Moore.

Tom goes crazy in the final Vauxhall Monaro model, the VXR 500.

Pete Tong visits the Fifth Gear cafe to do a little off-road challenge in a Land Rover Defender.

Wayne Hemingway, founder of the Red or Dead fashion label, goes out on a lake with Tim in a 1960’s Amphicar.

Tiff and Vicki see who can go faster on the most powerful production motorcycle in the world, the Kawasaki ZZR1400.

Jonny Smith sees if he can mow more lawn in a Volkswagen Touareg pulling a mower than the world’s largest mower, the £250,000 Claas Cougar.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview:
Jason takes to the track in a Litchfield Type 25 Impreza, a highly tuned Subaru Impreza WRX STi which is based on a version of the Impreza that’s only available in Japan and that’s the base for the Group N rally car.

Since golfer Ian Poulter’s new Ford GT is not yet street legal, Tim Lovejoy arranges for him to test another Ford GT on a track.

Vicki takes a look at the Volkswagen Golf GT which has both a turbocharger and a supercharger.

Jon Bentley finds out at what speed is the best to go over a speed bump.

Tom drives the very quick, but rather bland BMW 335i Coupe.

Tiff drives a £170,000 Ferrari 599 GTB Fiorano in Bolivia on a leg of the Ferrari Panamerican challenge.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview:
Jason finds out if he can find an exciting used car for £9000 and then sell it for a profit.

Tiff drives the Lotus Exige 265E, a bio-ethanol powered car that ends up getting 50 HP more due to it’s fuel.

Tom checks out the new Volvo C30 Sports Coupe.

Exclusive behind the scenes of the car stunts in the next Bond movie, Casino Royale.

Vicki creates an ejector seat scene similar to the one from the Bond movie, Goldfinger.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview:
Tiff, a die hard German fan, tries to look at the Alfa Romeo 159 in a more Italian way.

Tim Lovejoy meets the new Bond star, Daniel Craig to find out more about Casino Royale, the cars in it, and Craig’s previous cars.

Tom drives the new Land Rover Freelander 2, to the most remote school in Britain.

Simon attempts to use the new Citroen C4 Picasso to recreate a famous Picasso painting in the sand.

Vicki takes on champion bike racers Leon Haslam, Jamie Whitham, Jamie Robinson and up and coming twins Alex and Sam Lowes in a Mini-Moto (little motorcycles) race 

Vicki tries waterskiing behing a motorbike.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview:
Jason attempts to sell the car he bought in an earlier episode for a profit.

Jonny Smith sees how fast the vegetable oil powered Mercedes-Benz from a previous episode can go.

Tom drives the new Mazda MX-5 Roadster Coupe, a hard-top convertible.

Previous winners of the giveaway cars are announced.

Tiff visits visits Mercedes-Benz World, the biggest car dealership in the country, and test drives Mercedes’ newest and most powerful 4×4, the ML 63 AMG.

Tim Lovejoy goes banger racing with comedian Alan Davies.

Vicki drives the new Porsche 911 GT3.

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview:
Behind the scenes of the Euro NCAP stars and how their crash tests are done.

Tim checks out the Piaggio MP3, a three wheeled scooter.

Tiff and Jason decide which is best — the new BMW Z4 Coupe or the new Audi TT.

Vicki gets a lesson from Terry Grant on how to drive on two wheels in a car.

Jonny Smith travels to the General Motors test facility in Germany to find out how car manufacturers test airbags by becoming a live test dummy.

Tom tries to pull a Boeing 747 with a stock Volkswagen Touareg, at the Top Gear test track and the plane from Casino Royale incidentally.

episodes.name: Episode 12
episodes.overview:
Tom drives a 4×4 that is greener than a Mini, the Honda CR-V.

Tim learns from stunt driver Russ Swift how to do the handbrake turn parking stunt.

Tiff uses an Audi S3 to give some tips on taking your own car to a track day.

Jon Bentley talks about how to buy a car wisely when it comes to depreciation.

Jonny enters a 0-60 MPH competition in the UK’s slowest-accelerating car, an 800cc Chevrolet Matiz.

Vicki takes a 15-year-old Daihatsu Charade out on a rally track.

episodes.name: Episode 13
episodes.overview:
Tiff drives the very quick 3 wheeled T-Rex.

Vicki takes Theo Paphitis out to test the £145,000 Mercedes S65 AMG.

The Fifth Gear Idol competition winner is revealed.

 

The Fifth Gear Awards 2006 where their top picks for best small car, best family car, best fast car, best overall car, and worst celebrity driver of the year.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview:
Jason takes the £230,000 Brabus Rocket, the fastest four-door car on the planet, to the German Autobahn to see if he can crack 200 MPH.

Vicki drives the new Fiat Panda 100HP and sees if it’s actually faster than a Ferrari (mind you, on a very small and tight track).

Jonny crashes a perfectly good Ford Focus into another Focus that had been previously crashed and repaired.

Tiff heads to Las Vegas to drive the totally awesome Audi R8.

Tom tests the new Kia Ceed by using to become a paparazzo.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview:
Tom drives the Alfa Romeo Spider around the Sahara desert.

What happens when you remove all of the oil from an engine? Fifth Gear finds out.

World Superbike leader James Toseland and Tiff Needell race around a track with a Honda Fireblade CBR 1000RR and the new Honda Civic Type R.

Jonny tests the new Mercedes C Class.

A motorcycle stunt team performs in the Fifth Gear parking lot.

Actor Chris Barrie gets to drive his dream car, an old Jaguar D-Type worth £3 million.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview:
Tom checks out the gadgets on the new Lexus LS460 and then sees if he can get the same gadgets for less on an older Lexus.

To test the durability of a windshield, Fifth Gear lobs chickens, rocks, and a road cone at one.

Jonny spends 12 hours locked in the new smart fortwo to see how comfortable it is.

Virgin Radio Breakfast Show DJ Christian O’Connell gets a stunt driving lesson from Russ Swift.

Vicki attempts to replicate the infamous C’était un rendez-vous using a diesel powered Citroën C3.

Tiff takes the new Bentley Continental GTC out with two models in the back to see if going faster makes their hair get blown around less.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview:
Tom and Jonny along with help from Tiff decide which hot hatch they like best — the Renault Megane F1 Team R26, the Mazda 3 MPS, the Ford Focus ST, the Honda Civic Type R, the Seat Leon Cupra, the Vauxhall Astra VXR, or the Volkswagen Golf Gti.

Fifth Gear drives a car to destruction in reverse to test it’s gearbox.

Comedian Paddy McGuinness does the CBT (Compulsory Basic Training) required for people who want to get a motorcycle permit.

Vicki tries to break 200 MPH in an A1 Grand Prix car.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview:
Tom drives the new Porsche Cayenne Turbo 

Vicki sees if she can live without a car for a day.

The Fifth Gear Shootout returns with the Renault Clio 197 taking on the brand new Vauxhall Corsa VXR.

Jonny drives a Rolls Royce Phantom to Italy for a classic car show at the Villa d’Este on Lake Como.

Yorkshire cricket captain Darren Gough goes head-to-head with Jason on an off-road track in a Volkswagen Touareg.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview:
Jonny drives the new Ford Mondeo, the most high-tech Ford you can buy (at least in the UK).

Driven To Destruction: Vicki finds out which cars are the most crash worthy by dropping them from a crane.

Shootout: Tiff races the Mini Cooper against the Suzuki Swift Sport.

Tom drives 1500 miles in the new BMW M5 Touring to Valencia, Spain to deliver some clothing to the Oracle America’s Cup team.

Olympic sprinter and BMX biker Iwan Thomas is tasked to do a stunt challenge with help from Russ Swift.

Jason Plato in the awesome sounding Aston Martin V8 Vantage Roadster.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview:
Tom drives the latest Land Rover Defender around Iceland to a glacier.

Jason and Tiff race a Ford GT against a Formula Ford with 150 horsepower.

Driven To Destruction: Vicki chains a car to a heavy truck and trashes it about from a cold start.

Fifth Gear visits the home of Alex James, the bass player in Blur, where he goes bungee jumping from a crane.

Jonny drives to Italy in a Ferrari 612 Scaglietti to deliver a birthday cake to Ferrari’s CEO.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview:
Jason tests the recently facelifted Jaguar XJR by dressing up for the part of a common Jaguar owner.

Dom Joly, creator of Trigger Happy TV, rents a tank for the day to drive around his home village.

Vicki drives the new Vauxhall VXR8 to the limit 

Tom and Jonny take two Reliant Robins and modify them to their liking for racing against each other.

Tiff finds out which is quicker around Castle Combe, the street legal Porsche 911 GT3 RS or the Porsche 911 GT3 Cup race car.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview:
Fifth Gear Shootout: Renault Sport Megane 230 F1 R26 versus one-off Ford Transit Connect X-press.

Yvette Fielding, British televesion presenter and owner of 3 Aston Martins, gets to drive her dream car, a Chesil Speedster — a replica of the rare Porsche 356 Speedster.

DTM driver Susie Stoddart races her DTM Mercedes-Benz race car against her company car, a Mecedes-Benz CL63 AMG.

Jonny races the Fifth Gear chip-fat powered Merecedes-Benz against a Jaguar powered by methane created from rotting apples.

Jason tests the brand new Lotus 2 Eleven, a very, very quick track day car.

Tom finds out what happens when a Limo crashes into a concrete barrier.

Vicki tests the latest BMW X5 by towing a wakeboarder.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview:
Fifth Gear Shootout: Tiff trashes two rental cars around, a Vauxhall Astra and a Ford Focus, to see which is faster.

Tom spends a day with wheel clampers to find out ways to beat them.

Vicki drives the latest generation Nissan 350Z 

A very short Q&A with John Travolta about his passion for cars.

Jonny, under the cover of darkness, fills in a pothole himself.

Tiff and Jason take four car loving cast members of the British soap opera Hollyoaks out for a series of boys vs. girls challenges 

Various motorcycle stunts in the cafe’s parking lot including stunts by Shane Lynch.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview:
Shootout: Vicki races the brand new Audi S5 against the BMW 335i.

Jason teaches Kyran Bracken how to drive on a track and then lets him have a go in an open-wheeled Formula Palmer Audi race car.

Tom drives the new Maserati GranTurismo coupe on some beautiful roads in Italy.

Jonny drives the incredibly small, but expensive, 4-door Mitsubishi “i” and then tries to get the same thing for less money by bolting two Smart cars on top of each other which ends in a hilarious result.

Tiff heads to the French chateau where the Bugatti Veyron is assembled and gets to drive one on both the streets and the track where he gets it a bit sideways!

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview:
Vicki compares the new Peugeot 207 GTi against a classic Peugeot 205 GTi to see if it really does live up to the old car.

Jonny road tests the new £350,000, 207mph Mercedes-Benz McLaren SLR Roadster.

Tiff and Jason put the Audi R8 and the Porsche 911 Carrera 4S head-to-head.

Fifth Gear meets up with Paddy McGuinness once again as he prepares for and takes his motorcycle test.

Man looks at what happens when a big, 15 year old Volvo 940 estate crashes into a small, light, 3 year old Renault Modus which has a 5 star Euro NCAP safety rating.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview:
Australian cricket player Shane Warne gets a track driving lesson from Jason.

Fifth Gear Shootout: Vicki races the UK spec Honda Civic Type R against the harder core Japanese version.

Tom and Jonny put the new Mini Cooper D (diesel) against the petrol version to see which is better.

Tiff races the new Lamborghini Gallardo Superleggera head-to-head against British superbike racer Leon Haslam on a Ducati 1098.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview:
Vicki finds out if a police driver is as fast as a racing driver by spending a day with a police trainer.

Jason takes Sarah Beeny out in a Volvo Globetrotter semi-truck and challenges her to a maneuverability trial.

Tiff goes powersliding in the brand new BMW M3.

Jonny finds out if some of Britain’s cheapest cars can make it to the top of Britain’s steepest road when fully loaded.

Tom gets his hands on the keys to a Phantom Drophead Coupe and offers the car’s services out on a local radio station to good causes.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview:
Shootout: Vicki drives two Audi TTs — one with a manual gearbox, one with the semi-automatic double-clutch S-Tronic system — to see which is quickest around a track.

Fifth Gear puts fuel additives to the test to scientifically see if they really do improve engine performance or not.

Tom Ford drives the brand new Fiat 500 

Tiff takes the £225,000, 224 MPH Gumpert Apollo out on the track.

Jason goes offroading in the latest Bowler beast, the Nemesis.

Jonny meets up once again with the owner of the world’s fastest street legal car, a Vauxhall Victor named “Red Victor 1″, to see if they can break the quarter mile record.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview:
Vicki takes Sally Boazman, Radio 2’s traffic announcer, out for a day at Bentley’s chauffeur school.

Jonny celebrates the 75th anniversary of the Deuce Coupe, the chopped and tuned versions of the 1932 Ford Model B.

Fifth Gear crashes the annual gathering of fast cars trying to beat the 0-60 MPH record to see if anyone can beat the current record of 3.07 seconds.

Tiff and Jason put the BMW Z4 and Nissan 350Z head to head on the track.

Jonny test the new Mini Clubman in Madrid 

Tom drives an insane Smart Car monster truck which uses Unimog parts.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview:
Shootout: a “General Lee” Dodge Charger vs. a Ford Gran Torino from “Starsky and Hutch”.

Jonny and Tom build drift cars from a pair of Bedford Rascal vans which ends in a bad crash.

Tiff drives the brand new Subaru Impreza and sees if it lives up to it’s ancestors.

Jason drives the Caparo T1, a street legal race car, which ends in the car catching on fire and burning Jason.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview:
To celebrate the 100th anniversary of the Rolls-Royce Silver Ghost, Tom and Jonny build an armored version of one.

Tiff heads to Ferrari’s test track in Modena to see if the new Ferrari 430 Scuderia is faster than a Ferrari Enzo.

Fifth Gear Awards including best small car, best family car, best fast car, and best overall car of the year.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview:
Tom heads to an auction of Bernie Ecclestone’s private car collection. Jonny takes a Citroën C-Crosser and a Citroën 2CV to a field to see how the two fair offroad. Jason takes Mercedes-Benz CLK 53 AMG Black Series to Silverstone. Tiff teaches TV chef Heston Blumenthal how to powerslide his BMW M5.

Shootout: Vicki puts the Lotus Exige S against the Caterham CSR at Anglesey.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview:
Tom tests the all new Toyota Landcruiser. Jonny drives the new lightweight Mazda 2. Tiff and Jason put the BMW M3 and the Mercedes-Benz C63 AMG head-to-head.  Vicki learns how a Hollywood-style car barrel roll is done.

Shootout: Renault Clio 197 R27 versus Rage Buggy R180RT.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview:
Tom and Jonny enter a 100 year old gruelling 24 hour off-road driving event called the Exeter Trial in an old Volkswagen Beetle. Tiff tests the all-new Audi A3 Cabriolet to see if it can change his opinion of convertibles. Children under the age of 3 can travel in the back of a taxi with no child seat, so Fifth Gear crashes a taxi to find out just how unsafe this practice really is. The new Maserati GranTurismo is coming to the UK, so Jason takes it out for a spin.

Shootout: an eighteen year old Lotus Carlton versus it’s modern day equivalent, the Vauxhall VXR8.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview:
Fifth Gear checks out London’s most exclusive supercar rental club, the Segrave Clubparks, and parks three of their cars — a Lamborghini Murcielago LP640, a McLaren Mercedes SLR, and a Porsche Carrera GT — on the street for 10 minutes each to see which turns the most heads. Jonny takes a BMW 635d, the world’s first diesel grand tourer, to Poland in search of cheap diesel. Tom goes offroading in a Unimog U500. Tiff tests James Bond’s latest car, the Aston Martin DBS.

Shootout: fast van shootout with the Volkswagen Transporter Sportline against the Mercedes Vito X.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview:
Travis Pastrana talks about his experiences in Freestyle Motocross and rally racing. Tom tests the Land Rover Freelander and Nissan X-Trail at the Kinnaird estate in Perthshire, Scotland. Jonny goes looking for the ultimate first car for under £2400, the average spent on such a car. Tiff and Jason put the Porsche Cayman and BMW 135i Coupe head-to-head.

Shootout: Renault Twingo GT versus Fiat Panda 100HP, two entry-level hot hatches.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview:
Volkswagen camper van comparison: Tom and Jonny test the retro Danbury Rio against the modern Volkswagen California. Jason on the track in the new Nissan GT-R. Tom finds out what happens when a 5 star crash rating car crashes into a tree. Tiff in Audi’s most powerful production car, the Audi RS6 Avant, a station wagon.

Shootout: Mini One versus Fiat 500.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview:
Jason goes offroading with England rugby captain, Phil Vickery. Vicki compares the new electric powered Smart ED to it’s gasoline powered counterpart, the Smart FourTwo. Tom Ford heads up to the Arctic Circle for some extreme testing of the new Volvo XC70. Tiff takes the all new the Lexus IS F out onto a track.

Shootout: Ford Fiesta ST versus Vauxhall Corsa SRi.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview:
Jason takes British downhill skier Chemmy Alcott offroading in a Group N rally car. Tom Ford drives the new Citroën C5 in Lisbon. Tiff and Jonny go behind the scenes of the 50th NASCAR Daytona 500.

Shootout: Porsche Cayenne GTS versus BMW X5 SE.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview:
Jonny tries to find some sexy coupes for less than £1500. Vicki pushes Bentley’s fastest ever production car, the 200 mph Continental GT Speed, to the limit. Tiff drives a NASCAR race car around a track. Tom Ford tests Jaguar’s make or break executive saloon, the XF. Jason finds out if the Lotus Elise SC, the first model to be fitted with a supercharger, is the best version ever.

Shootout: Volkswagen Golf GTi versus Subaru Impreza WRX.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview:
Tiff sideways in the brand new Subaru WRX STi. Jonny heads to the Geneva Motor Show. Tom joins a Welsh mountain rescue team for the day to put the Hummer H3 through its paces. Tiff and Jason pit the Mini Cooper S Works and the Renault Clio Cup against each other to find out which is best.

Shootout: Ford Focus RS versus Ford Escort Cosworth.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: World snooker champion Ronnie O’Sullivan asked Fifth Gear to help him choose a new car to spend his winnings on, so Vicki takes him out onto the track in a Mercedes C63 AMG and a BMW M3. Tiff and Jason put the Mitsubishi Evo X FQ300 and the Subaru Impreza WRX STi head-to-head on the track. Tom tests Ford’s new SUV, the Kuga, by driving it on snow, road and mud. Jonny investigates if cars are worth more as scrap than as a functioning car. Tiff tries out the world’s first underwater car, the Rinspeed Squba, which was inspired by James Bond’s white Lotus Esprit in “The Spy Who Loved Me”.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview:
Tim investigates why it can cost up to £200 just to change a headlight bulb on a Renault Mégane. Vicki spends a day with Lewis Hamilton at the Brooklands Motoring Festival. Jonny sees what kinda car you can get if you swore off drinking alcohol for 3 years and saved the money instead. Jason goes powersliding in the new Porsche 911 GT2. Tom drives the new Mercedes-Benz SL63 AMG, crash tests a second-hand convertible in a rollover crash.

Shootout: Tiff puts the latest Mazda RX-8 against the Nissan 350Z.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: F1 driver Jarno Trulli tries to get the most out of the hybrid Toyota Prius. Jason Plato pits the Volkswagen Passat R36 against the Audi A4 3.0 TDi in a contest of petrol power and diesel torque.  Tim Shaw tests the acceleration claims of a range of performance motors. Tiff Needell competes with world speedway champion Jason Crump in a race of car versus bike.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview:
Tim shows some loopholes in the new 2009 UK car tax code. Jonny sees if the new Volkswagen Passat CC can match the Mercedes-Benz CLS 500 in terms of refinement. Tom drives the new seemingly-pointless BMW X6. Jonny examines the new Citroen Berlingo Multispace’s practicality by turning it an ice cream van at an amusement park. Vicki heads to the Goodwood Festival of Speed to race the electric Tesla Roadster and the Breckland Beira. Tiff in the crazy KTM X-Bow.

Shootout: Jason pits the Honda Civic Mugen RR, imported from Japan, against the Honda S2000.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview:
Tiff and Jason put the BMW M3 and the Lexus ISF head-to-head to see which is faster and more exciting with some help from some girls. Tom sees if the new Subaru Forester is as good as the Land Rover Freelander 2, the benchmark in small SUVs. Bruno Senna, nephew of F1 driver Ayrton Senna, is a special guest presenter this week and compares the Porsche 911 Turbo to the Nissan GT-R on the track. Vicki participates in the Subaru convoy in tribute to the late Colin McRae. Tom drives the Dodge Challenger SRT-8. Jason teaches John Prescott to drive a race spec Jaguar XKR.

Shootout: Vicki in the Vauxhall Astra Nurburgring and the Ford Focus ST.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview:
Tom drives the new Volkswagen Scirocco around Wales. Jonny compares the Hyundai i800 to the Chrysler Grand Voyager. Tim investigates people who call up car sellers offering to help sell their car for a fee. Jason teaches Moto GP star James Toseland to drift in the new Aston Martin V8 Vantage. Jonny finds out if new Jeep Wrangler is better or worse than a Willys Jeep from World War II. Tiff attempts to set an alternative-powered quarter mile record in a Lotus Exige 270E TriFuel.

Shootout: Vicki in the brand new Porsche Boxster RS60 Spyder and a last-generation Porsche 911 Carrera 2.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview:
Jonny updates a Volkswagen Golf GTI Mk2 to more modern standards.

Tim compares how different prices tires affect stopping distances.

Tom drives the new Mk7 Ford Fiesta.

Simon Pavey puts Tiff and Vicki through a series offroad motorcycle challenges.

Jonny helps Light Welterweight boxer Ricky Hatton restore his Reliant Robin van used in the British sitcom Only Fools and Horses.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview:
Vicki tests the new Honda Jazz by using it as a support vehicle for The Tour of Britain, one of the United Kingdom’s biggest cycling events.

Tim finds out if he can service a modern car instead of paying to have a dealership do it.

Tom compares Renault’s new Laguna GT sporting four wheel steering to the Ford Mondeo.

Tiff and Jason race head-to-head in seriously quick go-karts.

Tom checks out the Fiat Grande Punto Abarth, a little hot hatch.

Jonny with help from Dirk “Face” Benedict of the A-Team compare a brand new Mercedes-Benz S-Class to a second hand one.

Jason sees if the top pilot of the Blue Eagles helicopter aerobatics squad is as good in a car as he is in his Lynx helicopter.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: New series. World champion boxer Joe Calzaghe and his glamour model girlfriend Jo-Emma Larvin take part in an off-road challenge with Tiff Needell, Johnny Smith examines the Volkswagen Golf Mk6, and Vicki Butler-Henderson takes the new Ferrari California for a test-drive in Italy. Plus, Tom Ford reviews the safety of a popular family vehicle and Tim Shaw assesses the effectiveness of automated car washes.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Olympic swimmer and Strictly Come Dancing contestant Mark Foster tests a supercharged Vauxhall VXR8, Jonny Smith watches classic vehicles being raced at the Firecracker Banger meet, and Tim Shaw retakes his driving test in a Nissan Micra. Plus, Vicki Butler-Henderson assesses the Smart MHD city car, Jason Plato compares two Renaults, and Tiff Needell examines the new Porsche 911.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Vicki Butler-Henderson chauffeurs comedian Bill Bailey to one of his West End gigs in a Mercedes that has been converted to run on nothing but chip fat. Tom Ford test-drives the new Kia Soul, while Jonny Smith presents his pick of reasonably priced cabriolets. Tiff Needell takes the new Lamborghini Gallardo LP560-4 for a spin and Tim Shaw investigates the savings to be made on new vehicles.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Jason Plato races the Maserati Gran Turismo with olympic cyclist Bradley Wiggins, Tiff Needell pits the Renault Megane R26.R against the Caterham CDX sports car and Vicki Butler-Henderson assesses the speed of the BMW 330d. Tim Shaw gives advice on protecting vehicles from theft, Jonny Smith reviews the new Ford Ka and Tom Ford tests the storage space in the Fiat Qubo with the help of a Guns 'N' Roses tribute band.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Tiff Needell and Jason Plato race the Volkswagen Scirocco and Mini Cooper S hatchback, Tom Ford finds out if he can fit into the world's tiniest four-seater, the Toyota iQ, and Tim Shaw tests car polishes. Jonny Smith reveals how cash-strapped families can afford to buy a second-hand SUV and Jason Plato meets Comedy Dave from the BBC Radio 1 breakfast show

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Jason Plato races the Maserati Gran Turismo with olympic cyclist Bradley Wiggins, Tiff Needell pits the Renault Megane R26.R against the Caterham CDX sports car and Vicki Butler-Henderson assesses the speed of the BMW 330d. Tim Shaw gives advice on protecting vehicles from theft, Jonny Smith reviews the new Ford Ka and Tom Ford tests the storage space in the Fiat Qubo with the help of a Guns 'N' Roses tribute band.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Olympic gold medal-winning sailors Sarah Ayton, Sarah Webb and Pippa Wilson race each other in the Ferrari F430 Scuderia, and Tiff Needell test-drives the Farbio GTS 400, Vicki Butler-Henderson pits the new Alfa Romeo Mito against the classic Mini, and Tim Shaw examines the diesel v petrol debate to find out which fuel offers the better value.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Charley Boorman tests modified cars powered by motorbike engines, Jonny Smith compares the fuel consumption of the Honda Insight with a standard diesel vehicle and Tiff Needell races two hatchbacks from the 1980s. Jason Plato reviews the new Ford Focus RS, Jonny Smith tries to make a profit at Europe's largest used-autoparts sale and Tim Shaw gives advice on speed-camera alerting systems. Last in the series.

episodes.name: Stunt Special
episodes.overview: An action-packed one-off special. Stuntman Steve Truglia prepares to perform a toy-car trick in a life-size vehicle fitted with Dunlop SP30's. He will attempt to defy gravity and neck-breaking G-forces to loop-the-loop.

episodes.name: Series 16, Episode 1
episodes.overview: Stuntman Steve Truglia tries to beat a world record by driving round the biggest loop-the-loop ever constructed. Retired Formula One competitor David Coulthard competes against Tiff Needell in an extreme van-driving challenge and Tim Shaw discovers whether buying an old banger results in cheap motoring. Tom Ford examines the Citroen C3 Picasso's suitability for a modern family man and Jonny Smith takes the Audi R8 V10 out on Spanish roads.

episodes.name: Series 16, Episode 2
episodes.overview: Tiff Needell teams up with former racing driver Stirling Moss to test the Ferrari 599 HGTE and Jonny Smith heads to Spain to discover whether the locals prefer the Audi A5 Cabriolet to the rival BMW 3 Series convertible. Jason Plato helps Olympic rowing gold medallist Matthew Pinsent find a sports car that accommodates his 6ft 5in frame, Tom Ford and Tiff Needell compete in the Ilkley Trial in West Yorkshire, and Tim Shaw investigates the accuracy of the combined economy cycle.

episodes.name: Series 16, Episode 3
episodes.overview: Tiff Needell and Jason Plato pit the new BMW Z4 against the Porsche Boxster, and Tim Shaw examines the Government's car-scrappage scheme. Comedian Ross Noble receives a day of trial-bike tuition from motorcyclist Dougie Lampkin, the team celebrates the joint birthday of the original Mini and the film The Italian Job, and Tom Ford gets behind the wheel of the Peugeot 308 CC.

episodes.name: Series 16, Episode 4
episodes.overview: Jason Plato pits the Mini Cooper Cabriolet against the Mazda MX-5, and Tim Shaw tries out the latest concept in car maintenance at a garage where equipment is supplied but the customers do the work themselves. Tom Ford assesses the performance of Toyota's new miniature SUV, the Urban Cruiser, and Jonny Smith is joined by Most Haunted's Derek Acorah for a ride in the Ghostbusters ambulance. Plus, Tiff Needell tests the Aston Marton V12 Vantage.

episodes.name: Series 16, Episode 5
episodes.overview: Tiff Needell and Jason Plato gain access to a variety of tanks, including a submersible Russian machine and a Chieftain, for a head-to-head battle. Jonny Smith follows the route of Dick Turpin in the new VW Golf GTi, Tom Ford and Radio 1 DJ Judge Jules test the Aston Martin DBS Volante and Tim Shaw investigates the damage that potholes do to cars. Plus, a look at the Evora - the first all-new Lotus for 13 years.

episodes.name: Series 16, Episode 6
episodes.overview: Tom looks at the idea of the national speed limit being lowered. Jason test drives the Renault Sport Clio 200. Jonny susses out the new Merc E-Class. Tiff finds out if the Caterham Roadsport 175 really works on the road and Jason drives the Lamborghini LP670-4 SV.

episodes.name: Series 16, Episode 7
episodes.overview: Jason and Tiff race a couple of double decker buses. John Barrowman is given lessons in rally-car driving. Jason test drives the new Audi TT RS. Tom drives the new Seat Exeo. Jonny reviews the Nissan Pixo and Tim tests "ecoRoute", a fuel saving application for Garmin GPS units.

episodes.name: Series 16, Episode 8
episodes.overview: Jason drives a couple of 1980s Cosworths. Jonny reviews the new Toyota Prius. Tom is offered the chance to ride in a Formula Ford race car but first he must fit the car's engine from a Focus. Tiff and Jonny find the best "Hot Hatchling". Tom drives the newest supercar - the Tramontana R Edition. James Martin is trained to drive a Formula 1 car.

episodes.name: Series 17, Episode 1
episodes.overview: Tiff and Vicki have been challenged to put four of the nippiest hatchbacks on the market to the test. Jonny examines a pair of city cars the Smart ForTwo and the Toyota iQ. Over in Italy, Jason gets behind the wheel of the supercar of the moment the Ferrari 458 Italia. Finally, Tiff talks to 2008 F1 World Champion Lewis Hamilton about the British supercar threatening to take Ferrari’s crown.

episodes.name: Series 17, Episode 2
episodes.overview: Tiff and Jason compare the Porsche 911 and Audi R8 V10 convertibles. Vicki examines the Nissan Cube in a new segment called “Need To Know”. Jonny reviews the very economical Volvo S80 DRIVe. Jason goes to the Italian Alps to drive the Lamborghini Gallardo LP570-4 Superleggera.

episodes.name: Series 17, Episode 3
episodes.overview: Vicki drives the new Maserati GranCabrio from Paris to Monaco. Shootout: Citroën DS3 DSport versus the Alfa Romeo MiTo Cloverleaf. Tiff and Jonny sees if electric cars are finally practical using the Mitsubishi i MiEV. Jason tries to break 200 MPH in the Noble M600 supercar.

episodes.name: Series 17, Episode 4
episodes.overview: Shootout: Jason pits the Nissan 370Z Roadster against the BMW Z4. Jonny compares the Skoda Superb Estate to other estates the Mercedes-Benz W124, the new Mercedes-Benz E250, and the Volvo 850R. Tiff drives the 4 door Aston Martin Rapide. Vicki drag races the new Rolls-Royce Ghost.

episodes.name: Series 17, Episode 5
episodes.overview: Ross Noble and Charlie Boorman join Tiff and Jason to play with some offroad toys, Jason drives the Porsche 911 GT3 RS, Vicky puts Mercedes' "Air Cap" to the test on an E-class convertible and Jonny drives the Audi A8.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Tiff tests out the Lexus LFA, Vicky shows us some new toys on the  BMW 535i, Jason compares the Mercedes-Benz E63 AMG to the Audi RS6 and Jonny looks at Volvo's crash test lab.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Tiff pushes the SLS AMG to the limit, Vicky susses out the new Lotus Elise then puts a Landcruiser head-to-head with the Land Rover Discovery with Jonny, and Jason rings the neck of the Ferrari 599 GTO.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Which is better, the VW Scirocco or Peugeot RCZ? Tiff finds out. Vicky looks at the Honda CR-Z, Jason hoons in the Camaro SS and Jonny joins Tiff for the famous Ilkley Trial.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: Jason drives the Morgan Aero SuperSports. Jonny goes to Germany to drive the Nissan Juke. Shootout: Tiff races the Volkswagen Golf R against the SEAT León Cupra R. Vicki looks at Gordon Murray’s new car, the T.25.

episodes.name: Series 17, Episode 10
episodes.overview: Jason and Tiff put the Nissan GT-R and the Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution FQ-400 head-to-head. Jonny reviews the new Audi A1. Tiff drives the electric Tesla Roadster S. Vicki judges some cars at the Salon Privé supercar show.

episodes.name: Series 18, Episode 1
episodes.overview: Tiff and Jason put the sportier versions of BMW M3 and the Mercedes-Benz C63 AMG head-to-head.  Ex-Stig Ben Collins goes drag racing in a mid-level dragster.  Vicki drives the Bentley Continental SuperSports Convertible on “one of the best roads in Europe” in Northern Ireland.  Jonny attempts to set some small engine speed records using a Skoda Fabia vRS

episodes.name: Series 18, Episode 2
episodes.overview:
Jason continues his racing lessons on the track with newbie petrolhead Comedy Dave from BBC Radio 1, using an Aston Martin Vantage N420 Roadster.  Jonny gets a ride in Europe's fastest street-legal car.  Vicki heads to the glamorous Paris Motor Show and shows us the top five cars of the show.

Shootout: Tiff puts the Porsche Cayman head-to-head against the Lotus Evora.

episodes.name: Series 18, Episode 3
episodes.overview: Tiff offers a unique behind-the-scenes glimpse of the final British Touring Car Championship race of the year as Jason attempts to clinch the title. Elsewhere, Vicki reveals everything you need to know about Renault's sexy new convertible the Wind, Jonny heads to the amazing scenery of Europe's highest road in Audi's super hi-tech RS5 and Tiff gets behind the wheel of the amazing Pagani Zonda R hypercar.

episodes.name: Series 18, Episode 4
episodes.overview: Tiff tests a Vauxhall against an Audi. Vicki takes a closer look at the new luxury SUV. Jason test drives an Audi supercar whilst Jonny enters his first ever competitive trackday event.

episodes.name: Series 18, Episode 5
episodes.overview: Tiff and Jason team up with F1 aces Johnny Herbert and Karun Chandhok for the ultimate dogfight. Vicki reveals all about Vauxhall's new compact MPV.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Jason experiences a cutting-edge Formula One driving simulator, Ben and Jonny perform a two-wheel driving stunt, Tiff races two stylish coupes and Vicki gets behind the wheel of the multimillion-pound Aston Martin DB5, as driven by James Bond in Goldfinger.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Ben Collins competes against Jason on the track. Robert Llewellyn tests the eco-friendly Nissan Leaf. Tiff test drives two green yet fast coupes. Vicki takes a drive in the Volvo S60 saloon.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: Jonny and Ben perform a two-wheel driving stunt, Vicki puts a radical new four-door Mini through its paces, Jason teaches ex-rugby player Matt Dawson wet-weather driving techniques in a supercar and Tiff wrestles with two mean American muscle cars.

episodes.name: Series 18, Episode 10
episodes.overview:
Vicki Butler-Henderson introduces the motoring show's annual awards ceremony honouring the best cars of the year. Tiff Needell, Jason Plato and Ben Collins have a three-way contest in similarly matched sports cars, and the presenters take a look back at the highlights of 2010. 

Last in the series.

episodes.name: Series 19, Episode 1
episodes.overview: Tiff and Jason drive the Yas Marina in Abu Dhabi, and Vicki zips around the Monaco in a £40,000 hot hatch. Back in Britain, Jonny meets an ingenious car engineer, and in the Team Test, the foursome reviews the BMW X3 four-wheel drive.

episodes.name: Series 19, Episode 2
episodes.overview: Jason takes the new Aston Martin supercar for a spin in Spain, Tiff tries his hand at ice-driving in Lapland, Jonny drives the Atlantic Road in Norway in the new Citroen DS3 Racing and Vicki test-drives the limited edition BMW M3 GTS.

episodes.name: Series 19, Episode 3
episodes.overview: In this episode of Fifth Gear, Tiff tests a new estate car from Ferrari, Vicki puts two luxurious diesels saloons against each other on the track, Jason is in Abu Dhabi trying out the fastest motorsport on earth – drag racing, and the whole team test the newest version of Nissan’s little Micra.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Jason and Tiff race a pair of super cars. Vicki travels to southern Spain to test drive the new BMW's new convertible. Johnny takes a look at the intricacies of the Nürburgring track in Germany.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Vicki test drives the new super-charged Lotus Evora. Tiff and Jonny end up going hill-climbing. The brand new Audi A7 is pushed to it's limits.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Tiff and Jason are at the 50th birthday party of the E- Type Jag. Vicki discovers just how sharp James Martin is with a knife. The team decide whether the Lexus has got the balance right with its new luxury hybrid.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Tiff and Jason take a look at some exciting new cars and take part in a series of high octane stunts that will push the team to their limits. Tiff Needell tests the 1M coupe in the hills of the Scottish countryside.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Tiff and Jason get a chance to test drive the new 205mph McLaren MP4-12C, comparing it with the Ferrari 458 Italia. Vicki gets a chance to become a driver of action with the help of Hollywood legend Vic Armstrong.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: Tiff is in the stunning roads above Nice in the South of France to test the £185,000 Lamborghini Gallardo Performante, Jason tests the Porsche Cayman R around Britain’s fastest race track, Jonny reveals the cars you should buy if you’re interested in “free motoring”, and the team come together to test the updated luxury limousine from Volkswagen, the Phaeton.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: In this tenth-anniversary special, the presenters look back at some of their most memorable moments. Jonny attempts the Isle of Man TT circuit on a three-wheeled scooter, and Tiff and Vicki test two of the most exciting cars on the market – the BMW M3 GTS and the Porsche 911 GT3 RS.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: The team conduct a shocking 120mph crash test, pit the two most powerful Jaguars ever head to head, blast through mega-fashionable Croatia in a £150,000 Bentley and get to grips with the car everyone's talking about - the Range Rover Evoque.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Tiff chats to British rally legend Mark Higgins. The presenters take a look at a new Mercedes convertible. Vicki races a new Ford Mustang around Le Mans. Jonny begins a journey of a lifetime in a very unlikely car.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Tiff test drives Lamborghini's new Aventador hypercar. Vicki makes her way through Italy's snowy mountain roads in Mini's brand new Coupe. Jonny finds out about car culture's biggest phenomenon, vehicle wrapping.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Vicki test drives the new Ferrari 458 Spider convertible in Maranello Italy.  Tiff completes another Fifth Gear shoot out between two uber coupes, the 444bhp Audi RS5 and the 451bhp  Mercedes C63 AMG Coupe. Johnny's in France to test Citroen's new radical DS5 hybrid car.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Tiff's on the limit in a very special Porsche 911 the 500bhp RS 4.0 of which a limited production run of only 600 will be made.  Vicki test drives the maddest hybrid we have ever seen in the one of a kind Honda CRV tweaked by tuning company Mugen which cost 150K. Johnny's in Portugal to test the new Renault hybrid car the Fluence.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Jonny finds the best driving road in the world. Vicki takes the new VW Amarok pick-up for a test drive on a beach in Portugal. The driving skills of Roy Keane are tested by Tiff at the Nurburgring. The presenters take a look at the new BMW 1 series (F20).

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview:
Tiff takes a drive through France's Champagne region in Aston Martin's newest convertible. 

Vicki is the umpire in a race between two England cricket stars.

Jonny takes a look at two off-road bargains to help see us through the winter.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Jonny drives a brand new version of one of Britain's most important cars. Tiff puts England cricket legend Jimmy Anderson through his paces around the gruelling Nurburgring race track. The team test the latest version of the iconic Jeep.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: Motoring magazine show with Tiff Needell, Vicki Butler-Henderson and Jonny Smith. Vicki blasts through the Pyrenees in the brand new BMW M5, Jonny heads to Barcelona to drive SEAT's new city car, the team test the Mercedes G-Class and Tiff is joined by rally ace Mark Higgins to test Renault's new hatch.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: Jonny takes a look at some exciting cars at the LA motorshow. Ian Botham is taught how to drive around the legendary Nurburgring racing track. Vicki learns some evasive driving techniques from the police who chauffeur the Royal Family.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: The return of the motoring magazine, with presenters Tiff Needell, Vicki Butler-Henderson, Jason Plato and Jonny Smith reviewing cars and taking on challenges.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Stig Blomquist takes Jonny Smith for a drive on ice, and the convertible Mercedes SLS AMG is pitted against an Aston Martin, a Jaguar and a Bentley.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: The team races a Radical sports car against the Ariel Atom in Anglesey. Vicki Butler-Henderson visits the Monaco Motor Show and there is a look at the safest second-hand cars.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Tiff Needell takes to the Italian F1 circuit in the hope of qualifying for the Lamborghini Series, and the team reports whether different types of petrol affect a car's performance.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Jason Plato races Formula Off-Road buggies in Iceland, Tiff Needell tests the new Bentley Continental GT, and a Rolls-Royce is cleaned at the world's most expensive car wash.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Tiff Needell celebrates the Ferrari F40's 25th birthday, Jason Plato pits the Mercedes C63 AMG Black Series against its BMW rival and Vicki Butler-Henderson drives a new Land Rover.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Jonny Smith takes a behind-the-scenes look at the Isle of Man TT motorbike race with John McGuinness, and the Subaru BRZ sports car is tested around the circuit.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Jonny Smith examines Ferraris' latest supercar, the F12berlinetta, while Vicki Butler-Henderson explores the world of motorbike speedway in Denmark.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: Jonny Smith heads to Sweden for an American car show, Tiff Needell tests the KTM X-Bow R trackday car, and Jason Plato explores affordable ways to upgrade a car stereo.

episodes.name: Fifth Gear.S22E01
episodes.overview: Vicki in the new Porsche Boxster S against a jet plane, Tiff tests the difference between used and new tyres. Jonny goes to Trollstigen to test Ford Focus ST. Jason tests Audi S8.

episodes.name: Fifth Gear.S22E02
episodes.overview: Jason tests the brand new Pagani Huayra, Tiff tests the new Porsche 911 cabriolet to find out if it's quicker than the Audi R8 Spyder. Vicki tests a super car off roader. Johny reveals the three classic cars that could be a better investment than gold.

episodes.name: Fifth Gear.S22E03
episodes.overview: Vicki in the brand new Porsche Panamera GTS against the all-new Mercedes CLS 63, both cars are tested to the limit. Jason tests a brand new supercar made in the Netherlands. Johny spends a night in the Swiss alps to demonstrate how your car can keep you alive. Tiff tests the Frontline MG LE50.

episodes.name: Fifth Gear.S22E04
episodes.overview: Tiff and rally driver Kris Meeke find the ultimate hot hatch (VW Golf GTI vs Renault Sport Megane vs Ford Focus ST vs Astra VXR), Vicki is in Germany to test the Audi RS 4, Jonny finds out how the world's most powerful simulator has become F1's secret weapon. Jason reveals the ultimate second-hand sports car you can buy on a budget.

episodes.name: Fifth Gear.S22E05
episodes.overview: Jonny jumps into the world of professional drifting, the team test the Audi S7 to the extreme, Vicki takes part in a world record attempt: the largest parade of Ferraris, Tiff tests filling tyres with nitrogen and Jason tests the new Mercedes SL.

episodes.name: Fifth Gear.S22E06
episodes.overview: Vicki races rally driver Andreas Mikkelsen in three speed challenges, Jason tests the new BMW M6, Tiff finds out what the ultimate small car is and Jonny shows the essential DIY skills that will allow you to save money.

episodes.name: Fifth Gear.S22E07
episodes.overview: Vicki tests the new Ferrari F12 Berlinetta, Jonny attempts to become the fastest drag race passenger, Tiff and Jason race each other in a dog fight find to find out which of the latest entry level hot hatches is the greatest, and the team test the latest car safety systems.

episodes.name: Fifth Gear.S22E08
